#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.216"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.216:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.216:0.2"
msgid "22. Akkosakavagga"
msgstr "22. Abuse"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.216:0.3"
msgid "216. Dutiyaakkhantisutta"
msgstr "216. Intolerance (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.255"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.216:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā akkhantiyā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of intolerance."

msgctxt "an5.216:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.216:1.3"
msgid ""
"Bahuno janassa appiyo hoti amanāpo, luddo ca hoti, vippaṭisārī ca, sammūḷho "
"kālaṃ karoti, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"Most people find you unlikable and unlovable. You’re cruel and remorseful. "
"You feel lost when you die. And when your body breaks up, after death, you’"
"re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "an5.216:1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā akkhantiyā."
msgstr "These are the five drawbacks to intolerance."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.216:2.1"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā khantiyā."
msgstr "There are these five benefits of tolerance."

msgctxt "an5.216:2.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.216:2.3"
msgid ""
"Bahuno janassa piyo hoti manāpo, aluddo ca hoti, avippaṭisārī ca, asammūḷho "
"kālaṃ karoti, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"Most people find you likable and lovable. You’re neither cruel nor "
"remorseful. You don’t feel lost when you die. And when your body breaks up, "
"after death, you’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "an5.216:2.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā khantiyā”ti."
msgstr "These are the five benefits of tolerance.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.216:2.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
